ARP Help? Data that travels over the air and how to protect (or decipher) it
Post a reply
4 posts	• Page 1 of 1	ARP Help?
by I liek Trees on Wed Jun 15, 2011 10:18 pm	([msg=58574]see ARP Help?[/msg])
Hey everyone.I've been learning a lot about hacking over the past few weeks, and I decided to give it a try. I downloaded Cain from Oxid, and I started messing around with the ARP and sniffer. I am able to run my sniffer and the ARP tool, and I can see that I am poisoning the connection between the router and my other computer, but I have 2 problems.First, when I start poisoning the connection, I end up DOS'ing my other computer, meaning I am unable to sniff any passwords since it isn't sending any. How can I set my computer up to route the packets from the router to the target computer so it maintains an internet connection?Second, I have a 1397 WLAN Mini-card. I'm not sure if this wireless card supports promiscuous mode, and google isn't answering my question. Does anyone know if my card supports promiscuous mode, and if it does, how can I configure it to accept packets sent to other MAC addresses rather than just packets sent to it?
I liek Trees	New User
