by Goatboy on Thu Jun 16, 2011 2:46 am	([msg=58590]see Re: ARP Help?[/msg])
The ARP problem seems more like C&A is only poisoning in one direction. This is weird, because I am pretty sure it is supposed to poison in both. It could be that your router or other comp has some anti-poisoning protection, but I doubt this.As for the wifi card, you can download Wireshark and use it to check. That or aircrack-ng if you have a linux box lying around.
